## Task Completion:

**1. Analyze and Describe the Main Target Image:**

*   **Count & Layers:**
    *   The structure is composed of **14 blocks** in total.
    *   It is built in **3 distinct layers**.
        *   **Layer 1 (Bottom):** Consists of 3 red arch blocks, 3 green rectangular blocks, and 4 orange cylindrical blocks.
        *   **Layer 2 (Middle):** Consists of 3 yellow rectangular blocks, placed on top of the orange cylindrical blocks.
        *   **Layer 3 (Top):** Consists of 1 yellow semi-circular block, placed on top of the yellow rectangular blocks.

*   **Spatial Relationships:**
    *   **Left Section:** Three red arch blocks are placed side-by-side horizontally, forming a base. Three green rectangular blocks are placed on top of these red arch blocks, also side-by-side horizontally.
    *   **Right Section:** Four orange cylindrical blocks are arranged in a rectangular formation (2x2) as a base. Three yellow rectangular blocks are placed on top of these orange cylindrical blocks, arranged horizontally in a line. A single yellow semi-circular block is placed on top of the yellow rectangular blocks, seemingly in the center of the line.
    *   The left and right sections are placed adjacent to each other on the ground level.

**2. Select the Required Blocks from the Dictionary:**

*   **Needed Blocks and Indices:**
    *   Red Arch Block (Horizontal): Index **1** (Needed 3 times)
    *   Green Rectangular Block (Horizontal): Index **7** (Needed 3 times)
    *   Orange Cylindrical Block (Vertical): Index **12** (Needed 4 times)
    *   Yellow Rectangular Block (Horizontal): Index **11** (Needed 3 times)
    *   Yellow Semi-circular Block: Index **14** (Needed 1 time)
